Description: Fragment of neck and shoulder of East Greek pottery black-figured closed vase, probably an amphora; substantial ridge at top of shoulder; interior reserved; exterior slipped white: part of floral on neck above band; irregular dots on outside of ridge; tongues at top of shoulder, black-figure decoration of part of lion to right. Graffito on shoulder.
Curator's comments: Marked '50' and '2?' in pencil and 'List 50' on label.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.1189)
